01:28:05,191 --> 01:28:07,623
on gas, ropes, and new nets

1504
01:28:07,691 --> 01:28:10,626
and a brand-new shrimping boat.

1505
01:28:31,740 --> 01:28:35,174
<i>Now Bubba told me everything
he knew about shrimping,</i>

1506
01:28:35,241 --> 01:28:38,176
<i>but you know what I found out?</i>

1507
01:28:39,244 --> 01:28:41,803
<i>Shrimping is tough.</i>

1508
01:28:43,747 --> 01:28:46,408
I only caught five.

1509
01:28:46,482 --> 01:28:49,917
A couple more,
you can have yourself a cocktail.

1510
01:28:51,752 --> 01:28:54,686
Hey, you ever think about
naming this old boat?

1511
01:28:54,754 --> 01:28:57,687
It's bad luck to have
a boat without a name.

1512
01:28:57,755 --> 01:29:00,189
<i>I'd never named a boat before,</i>

1513
01:29:00,257 --> 01:29:05,283
<i>but there was only one
I could think of,</i>

1514
01:29:05,360 --> 01:29:09,317
<i>the most beautiful name
in the wide world.</i>

1515
01:29:13,399 --> 01:29:14,887
<i>~ Do a little dance ~</i>

1516
01:29:14,965 --> 01:29:16,933
<i>~ Make a little love ~</i>

1517
01:29:17,000 --> 01:29:21,298
<i>~ Get down tonight ~</i>

1518
01:29:21,369 --> 01:29:23,564
<i>~ Do a little dance ~</i>

1519
01:29:23,638 --> 01:29:25,399
<i>~ Make a little love ~</i>

1520
01:29:25,471 --> 01:29:27,098
<i>~ Get down tonight ~</i>

1521
01:29:27,173 --> 01:29:28,264
<i>~ Whoo ~</i>

1522
01:29:28,340 --> 01:29:29,637
<i>~ Get down tonight... ~</i>

1523
01:29:29,708 --> 01:29:32,107
<i>Now, I hadn't heard from Jenny</i>

1524
01:29:32,176 --> 01:29:33,472
<i>in a long while,</i>

1525
01:29:33,543 --> 01:29:35,977
<i>but I thought about her a lot.</i>

1526
01:29:36,046 --> 01:29:39,138
<i>I hoped whatever
she was doing made her happy.</i>

1527
01:29:39,213 --> 01:29:44,239
~ Oh, and the bird
you cannot change ~

1528
01:29:47,685 --> 01:29:54,384
~ And this bird
you cannot change ~

1529
01:29:54,456 --> 01:30:01,825
~ Lord knows I can't change ~

1530
01:30:01,894 --> 01:30:08,820
~ Lord, help me, I can't change ~

1531
01:31:25,010 --> 01:31:28,445
<i>I thought about Jenny all the time.</i>

1532
01:31:51,760 --> 01:31:53,851
Hey!

1533
01:32:17,375 --> 01:32:21,969
Lieutenant Dan,
what are you doing here?

1534
01:32:22,044 --> 01:32:25,410
Well, thought
I'd try out my sea legs.

1535
01:32:25,480 --> 01:32:28,414
Well, you ain't got no legs,
Lieutenant Dan.

1536
01:32:28,482 --> 01:32:29,914
Yes, I know that.

1537
01:32:29,982 --> 01:32:34,178
You wrote me a letter,
you idiot.

1538
01:32:34,251 --> 01:32:36,617
Well, well.
Captain Forrest Gump.

1539
01:32:36,687 --> 01:32:39,552
I had to see this for myself...

1540
01:32:40,856 --> 01:32:42,322
And...

1541
01:32:42,390 --> 01:32:46,825
I told you if you were ever
a shrimp boat captain,

1542
01:32:46,892 --> 01:32:48,826
that I'd be your first mate.

1543
01:32:48,894 --> 01:32:50,554
Well, here I am.

1544
01:32:50,628 --> 01:32:52,561
I'm a man of my word.

1545
01:32:52,629 --> 01:32:53,653
O.K.

1546
01:32:53,730 --> 01:32:55,889
But don't you be thinking

1547
01:32:55,964 --> 01:32:58,398
that I'm going
to be calling you "sir."

1548
01:32:58,466 --> 01:32:59,398
No, sir.

1549
01:33:07,938 --> 01:33:09,461
It's my boat.

1550
01:33:12,641 --> 01:33:16,736
I have a feeling
if we head due east,

1551
01:33:16,811 --> 01:33:20,370
we'll find some shrimp,
so take a left.

1552
01:33:21,781 --> 01:33:23,213
Take a left!

1553
01:33:23,281 --> 01:33:24,212
Which way?

1554
01:33:24,281 --> 01:33:25,213
Over there!

1555
01:33:25,282 --> 01:33:26,715
They're over there!

1556
01:33:26,784 --> 01:33:30,115
Get on the wheel
and take a left.

1557
01:33:30,185 --> 01:33:31,618
O.K.

1558
01:33:32,953 --> 01:33:34,887
Gump, what are you doing?

1559
01:33:34,955 --> 01:33:36,386
Take a left!

1560
01:33:36,455 --> 01:33:37,444
Left!

1561
01:33:39,324 --> 01:33:43,258
That's where we're going
to find those shrimp, my boy!

1562
01:33:43,326 --> 01:33:44,258
Ha ha!

1563
01:33:44,327 --> 01:33:46,453
That's where we'll find them.

1564
01:33:58,869 --> 01:34:00,802
Still no shrimp, Lieutenant Dan.

1565
01:34:00,870 --> 01:34:02,804
O.K., so I was wrong.

1566
01:34:02,872 --> 01:34:05,805
Well, how are we
going to find them?

1567
01:34:05,873 --> 01:34:09,898
Maybe you should
just pray for shrimp.

1568
01:34:09,975 --> 01:34:12,636
~ So pray that ~

1569
01:34:12,711 --> 01:34:15,975
~ I'm homeward bound... ~

1570
01:34:16,046 --> 01:34:18,741
<i>So I went to church every Sunday.</i>

1571
01:34:20,183 --> 01:34:22,115
<i>Sometimes Lieutenant Dan came, too,</i>

1572
01:34:22,183 --> 01:34:26,050
<i>though I think he left
the praying up to me.</i>

1573
01:34:40,561 --> 01:34:41,960
No shrimp.

1574
01:34:43,063 --> 01:34:45,996
Where the hell's
this God of yours?

1575
01:34:46,064 --> 01:34:48,498
<i>It's funny Lieutenant Dan said that</i>

1576
01:34:48,566 --> 01:34:52,435
<i>'cause right then God showed up.</i>

1577
01:35:08,076 --> 01:35:10,510
You'll never sink this boat!

1578
01:35:10,579 --> 01:35:13,239
<i>Now, me, I was scared,</i>

1579
01:35:13,313 --> 01:35:17,373
<i>but Lieutenant Dan, he was mad.</i>

1580
01:35:17,450 --> 01:35:18,438
Come on!

1581
01:35:20,984 --> 01:35:23,281
You call this a storm?

1582
01:35:23,352 --> 01:35:27,287
Come on, you son of a bitch!

1583
01:35:27,355 --> 01:35:31,289
It's time for a showdown!

1584
01:35:31,357 --> 01:35:32,824
You and me!

1585
01:35:32,892 --> 01:35:35,950
I'm right here!
Come and get me!

1586
01:35:36,027 --> 01:35:38,551
Ha ha! Ha ha!

1587
01:35:38,628 --> 01:35:40,061
You'll never sink...

1588
01:35:40,130 --> 01:35:41,426
This...

1589
01:35:41,497 --> 01:35:42,589
Boat!

1590
01:35:42,665 --> 01:35:44,598
Ha ha ha ha!

1591
01:35:44,666 --> 01:35:46,800
<i>Hurricane Carmen
came through here yesterday,</i>

1592
01:35:46,933 --> 01:35:48,729
destroying nearly
everything in its path.

1593
01:35:48,801 --> 01:35:51,734
And as in other towns
up and down the coast,

1594
01:35:51,802 --> 01:35:54,600
Bayou La Batre's
entire shrimping industry

1595
01:35:54,671 --> 01:35:57,002
<i>has fallen victim to Carmen</i>

1596
01:35:57,072 --> 01:35:59,904
<i>and has been left in utter ruin.</i>

1597
01:35:59,974 --> 01:36:01,406
<i>This reporter has learned,</i>

1598
01:36:01,475 --> 01:36:03,908
<i>in fact, only one shrimping boat</i>

1599
01:36:03,976 --> 01:36:05,499
<i>actually survived the storm.</i>

1600
01:36:05,577 --> 01:36:08,045
Louise. Louise, there's Forrest.

1601
01:36:08,113 --> 01:36:11,205
<i>After that, shrimping was easy.</i>

1602
01:36:11,281 --> 01:36:14,045
~ There will be great bounty ~

1603
01:36:14,117 --> 01:36:16,777
~ Oh, my God... ~

1604
01:36:16,851 --> 01:36:18,785
<i>Since people still
needed them shrimps</i>

1605
01:36:18,852 --> 01:36:21,217
<i>for shrimp cocktails
and barbecues and all</i>

1606
01:36:21,287 --> 01:36:24,221
and we were the only boat
left standing,

1607
01:36:24,289 --> 01:36:26,722
Bubba Gump shrimp's
what they got.

1608
01:36:26,790 --> 01:36:29,724
We got a whole bunch of boats.

1609
01:36:29,792 --> 01:36:31,725
<i>12 Jennys, big old warehouse.</i>

1610
01:36:31,793 --> 01:36:33,726
We even have hats

1611
01:36:33,794 --> 01:36:36,228
that say "Bubba Gump" on them.

1612
01:36:36,297 --> 01:36:37,728
Bubba Gump Shrimp.

1613
01:36:37,796 --> 01:36:39,229
It's a household name.

1614
01:36:39,298 --> 01:36:40,959
Hold on there, boy.

1615
01:36:41,033 --> 01:36:43,465
Are you telling me
you're the owner

1616
01:36:43,533 --> 01:36:45,763
of the Bubba Gump
Shrimp Corporation?

1617
01:36:45,836 --> 01:36:48,769
Yes. We got more money
than Davy Crockett.

1618
01:36:48,837 --> 01:36:51,771
Boy, I heard some whoppers
in my time,

1619
01:36:51,839 --> 01:36:54,773
but that tops them all.

1620
01:36:54,841 --> 01:36:56,808
Ha ha ha ha!

1621
01:36:56,875 --> 01:37:00,274
We were sitting
next to a millionaire.

1622
01:37:03,279 --> 01:37:08,271
Well, I thought it was
a very lovely story,

1623
01:37:08,349 --> 01:37:11,407
and you tell it so well,

1624
01:37:11,483 --> 01:37:13,575
with such enthusiasm.

1625
01:37:13,651 --> 01:37:17,745
Would you like to see
what Lieutenant Dan looks like?

1626
01:37:17,820 --> 01:37:20,050
Yes, I would.

1627
01:37:24,325 --> 01:37:25,952
That's him right there.

1628
01:37:28,194 --> 01:37:31,252
Let me tell you
something about Lieutenant Dan.

1629
01:37:31,329 --> 01:37:32,819
Forrest...

1630
01:37:38,000 --> 01:37:42,128
I never thanked you
for saving my life.

1631
01:38:07,317 --> 01:38:09,750
<i>He never actually said so,</i>

1632
01:38:09,819 --> 01:38:14,186
<i>but I think
he made his peace with God.</i>

1633
01:38:20,958 --> 01:38:23,756
<i>For the second time in 17 days,</i>

1634
01:38:23,828 --> 01:38:26,260
<i>President Ford escaped
possible assassination today.</i>

1635
01:38:26,328 --> 01:38:29,263
<i>Base to Jenny 1.
Base to Jenny 1.</i>

1636
01:38:29,331 --> 01:38:30,763
<i>Jenny 1. Go, Margo.</i>

1637
01:38:30,832 --> 01:38:32,765
<i>Forrest has a phone call.</i>

1638
01:38:32,833 --> 01:38:37,268
Yeah, well, you'll have
to tell them to call him back.

1639
01:38:37,335 --> 01:38:39,768
He is indisposed at the moment.

1640
01:38:39,837 --> 01:38:41,304
<i>His mama's sick.</i>

1641
01:39:00,383 --> 01:39:01,314
Where's Mama?

1642
01:39:01,383 --> 01:39:03,180
She's upstairs.

1643
01:39:05,619 --> 01:39:07,347
Hi, Forrest.

1644
01:39:08,421 --> 01:39:09,615
I'll see you tomorrow.

1645
01:39:09,689 --> 01:39:10,984
Oh, all right.

1646
01:39:17,359 --> 01:39:20,191
Sure got you straightened out,
didn't we, boy?

1647
01:39:32,369 --> 01:39:33,857
What's the matter, Mama?

1648
01:39:33,936 --> 01:39:37,099
I'm dying, Forrest.

1649
01:39:39,239 --> 01:39:42,139
Come on in, sit down over here.

1650
01:39:55,849 --> 01:39:57,975
Why are you dying, Mama?

1651
01:39:58,051 --> 01:40:00,143
It's my time.

1652
01:40:00,218 --> 01:40:03,277
It's just my time.

1653
01:40:03,354 --> 01:40:05,378
Oh, now...

1654
01:40:06,456 --> 01:40:09,014
Don't you be afraid,
sweetheart.

1655
01:40:09,090 --> 01:40:12,491
Death is just a part of life.

1656
01:40:12,560 --> 01:40:16,517
Something we're all
destined to do.

1657
01:40:16,595 --> 01:40:18,926
I didn't know it,

1658
01:40:18,997 --> 01:40:21,931
but I was destined
to be your mama.

1659
01:40:21,999 --> 01:40:24,727
I did the best I could.

1660
01:40:24,800 --> 01:40:26,734
You did good.

1661
01:40:26,802 --> 01:40:33,068
Well... I happen to believe
you make your own destiny.

1662
01:40:33,138 --> 01:40:37,664
You have to do the best
with what God gave you.

1663
01:40:41,177 --> 01:40:43,770
What's my destiny, Mama?

1664
01:40:43,845 --> 01:40:48,280
You're going to have
to figure that out for yourself.

1665
01:40:49,614 --> 01:40:52,549
Life is a box
of chocolates, Forrest.

1666
01:40:52,617 --> 01:40:55,550
You never know what
you're going to get.

1667
01:40:55,618 --> 01:40:58,552
<i>Mama always had a way
of explaining things</i>

1668
01:40:58,620 --> 01:41:00,553
<i>so I could understand them.</i>

1669
01:41:00,621 --> 01:41:02,088
I will miss you, Forrest.

1670
01:41:03,824 --> 01:41:06,087
<i>She had got the cancer</i>

1671
01:41:06,158 --> 01:41:08,091
<i>and died on a Tuesday.</i>

1672
01:41:08,159 --> 01:41:10,752
<i>I bought her a new hat</i>

1673
01:41:10,828 --> 01:41:12,852
<i>with little flowers on it.</i>

1674
01:41:15,798 --> 01:41:18,492
And that's all I have
to say about that.

1675
01:41:25,770 --> 01:41:28,465
Didn't you say you were waiting
for the number 7 bus?

1676
01:41:28,538 --> 01:41:31,267
There'll be another one
along shortly.

1677
01:41:34,775 --> 01:41:39,210
Now, because I had been
a football star and war hero

1678
01:41:39,277 --> 01:41:42,212
and national celebrity
and a shrimping boat captain

1679
01:41:42,280 --> 01:41:43,712
and a college graduate,

1680
01:41:43,781 --> 01:41:46,214
the city fathers
of Greenbow, Alabama,

1681
01:41:46,282 --> 01:41:48,772
decided to get together
and offered me a fine job.

1682
01:41:50,284 --> 01:41:53,810
<i>So I never went back to work
for Lieutenant Dan,</i>

1683
01:41:53,887 --> 01:41:56,821
<i>though he did take care
of my Bubba Gump money.</i>

1684
01:41:56,889 --> 01:41:59,823
<i>He got me invested
in some kind of fruit company.</i>

1685
01:41:59,891 --> 01:42:02,323
<i>So then I got a call from him</i>

1686
01:42:02,392 --> 01:42:04,952
<i>saying we don't have to worry
about money no more,</i>

1687
01:42:05,028 --> 01:42:09,429
and I said,
"That's good. One less thing."

1688
01:42:09,497 --> 01:42:11,293
~ I've got a new hope... ~

1689
01:42:11,364 --> 01:42:13,797
<i>Now Mama said
there's only so much fortune</i>

1690
01:42:13,866 --> 01:42:15,492
<i>a man really needs,</i>

1691
01:42:15,566 --> 01:42:18,966
<i>and the rest
is just for showing off.</i>

1692
01:42:19,036 --> 01:42:21,936
<i>So I gave a whole bunch of it</i>

1693
01:42:22,004 --> 01:42:25,267
<i>to the Foursquare Gospel Church...</i>

1694
01:42:25,339 --> 01:42:30,400
<i>and I gave a whole bunch to the
Bayou La Batre Fishing Hospital...</i>

1695
01:42:31,877 --> 01:42:34,310
<i>and even though Bubba was dead</i>

1696
01:42:34,378 --> 01:42:37,812
<i>and Lieutenant Dan said I was nuts,</i>

1697
01:42:37,880 --> 01:42:40,610
<i>I gave Bubba's mama Bubba's share.</i>

1698
01:42:43,984 --> 01:42:45,645
You know what?

1699
01:42:45,719 --> 01:42:49,653
<i>She didn't have to work
in nobody's kitchen no more.</i>

1700
01:42:49,721 --> 01:42:52,310
That smells wonderful.

1701
01:42:52,385 --> 01:42:54,815
<i>And 'cause I was a gozillionaire</i>

1702
01:42:54,884 --> 01:42:57,814
<i>and I liked doing it so much,</i>

1703
01:42:57,881 --> 01:43:01,311
<i>I cut that grass for free.</i>

1704
01:43:02,744 --> 01:43:06,174
<i>But at nighttime
when there was nothing to do</i>

1705
01:43:06,242 --> 01:43:08,672
<i>and the house was all empty,</i>

1706
01:43:08,740 --> 01:43:11,669
<i>I'd always think of Jenny.</i>

1707
01:44:15,123 --> 01:44:18,916
<i>And then... she was there.</i>

1708
01:44:51,628 --> 01:44:52,923
Hello, Forrest.

1709
01:44:52,994 --> 01:44:55,184
Hello, Jenny.

1710
01:45:06,018 --> 01:45:09,140
<i>Jenny came back
and stayed with me.</i>

1711
01:45:09,215 --> 01:45:12,144
<i>Maybe it was because
she had nowhere else to go,</i>

1712
01:45:12,963 --> 01:45:15,825
<i>or maybe it was because
she was so tired</i>

1713
01:45:16,321 --> 01:45:18,194
<i>'cause she went to bed
and slept and slept</i>

1714
01:45:18,772 --> 01:45:20,221
<i>like she hadn't slept in years.</i>

1715
01:45:22,209 --> 01:45:24,576
<i>It was wonderful
having her home.</i>

1716
01:45:24,646 --> 01:45:27,082
<i>Every day we'd take a walk,</i>

1717
01:45:27,151 --> 01:45:31,089
<i>and I'd jabber on
like a monkey in a tree,</i>

1718
01:45:31,157 --> 01:45:34,093
<i>and she'd listen about
Ping-Ponging and shrimping</i>

1719
01:45:34,161 --> 01:45:37,097
<i>and Mama making
a trip up to heaven.</i>

1720
01:45:37,165 --> 01:45:39,101
<i>I did all the talking.</i>

1721
01:45:39,169 --> 01:45:41,661
<i>Jenny most of the time
was real quiet.</i>

1722
01:46:21,334 --> 01:46:24,065
How could you do this?

1723
01:47:01,395 --> 01:47:05,891
<i>Sometimes I guess there
just aren't enough rocks.</i>

1724
01:47:07,403 --> 01:47:10,341
<i>I never really knew
why she came back,</i>

1725
01:47:10,409 --> 01:47:11,842
<i>but I didn't care.</i>

1726
01:47:11,910 --> 01:47:13,845
<i>It was like olden times.</i>

1727
01:47:13,913 --> 01:47:16,712
<i>We was like
peas and carrots again.</i>

1728
01:47:18,354 --> 01:47:20,790
<i>Every day,
I'd pick pretty flowers</i>

1729
01:47:20,858 --> 01:47:24,421
<i>and put them in her room for her,</i>

1730
01:47:24,497 --> 01:47:27,935
<i>and she gave me the best gift
anyone could ever get</i>

1731
01:47:28,002 --> 01:47:29,436
<i>in the wide world.</i>

1732
01:47:29,505 --> 01:47:32,031
They're made just for running.

1733
01:47:32,108 --> 01:47:33,371
<i>~ Carry me home to see my kin ~</i>

1734
01:47:36,047 --> 01:47:38,574
<i>And she even showed me
how to dance.</i>

1735
01:47:40,420 --> 01:47:42,788
<i>~ I miss ol'Bammy once again ~</i>

1736
01:47:42,858 --> 01:47:44,086
<i>~ And I think it's a sin ~</i>

1737
01:47:45,362 --> 01:47:47,024
<i>~ Sweet home Alabama... ~</i>

1738
01:47:47,098 --> 01:47:52,129
<i>Well, we was like family,
Jenny and me...</i>

1739
01:47:55,043 --> 01:47:58,242
<i>and it was the happiest time
in my life.</i>

1740
01:48:22,452 --> 01:48:23,886
You done watching it?

